<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idcbb8bdc2-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s41105"><num value="41105">§ 41105.</num><heading> Transfers of certificates</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idcbb8bdc3-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s41105/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">General</inline>.—</heading><content>A certificate issued under <ref href="/us/usc/t49/s41102">section 41102 of this title</ref> may be transferred only when the Secretary of Transportation approves the transfer as being consistent with the public interest.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idcbb8bdc4-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s41105/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Certification to Congress</inline>.—</heading><chapeau>When a certificate is transferred, the Secretary shall certify to the Committee on Commerce, Science, and Transportation of the Senate and the Committee on Transportation and Infrastructure of the House of Representatives that the transfer is consistent with the public interest. The Secretary shall include with the certification a report analyzing the effects of the transfer on—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idcbb8bdc5-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s41105/b/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> the viability of each carrier involved in the transfer;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idcbb8bdc6-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s41105/b/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> competition in the domestic airline industry; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idcbb8bdc7-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s41105/b/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> the trade position of the United States in the international air transportation market.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idcbb8bdc8-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/272/s1/e">Pub. L. 103–272, § 1(e)</ref>, <date date="1994-07-05">July 5, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/1121">108 Stat. 1121</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/104/287/s5/9">Pub. L. 104–287, § 5(9)</ref>, <date date="1996-10-11">Oct. 11, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/3389">110 Stat. 3389</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
